課程教材 Course Material
	    Rotational Invariance, Angular Momentum in 3 dimensions, Solution of rotationally-invariant problems 
Hydrogen atom (solution of eigenvalue problem, hydrogen spectrum, multi-electron atoms and Periodic table)
Spin
Addition of Angular Momentum (General problem, and Irreducible tensor operators)
Variational and Wentzel-Kramers-Brillouin (WKB) methods
Time-indpendent Perturbation Theory (Formalism, non-degenerate and degenerate perturbation theory) 
Time-dependent Perturbation Theory (First order and higher orders)
Scattering Theory (Introduction, Born Approximation, Partial Wave Expansion)
Supplementary Topics    

參考書目 References
	    1.(Main textbook): Principles of Quantum Mechanics (2nd Edition), by R. Shankar.  
2. Modern Quantum Mechanics (Revised Edition), by J. J. Sakurai.
3. Lectures on Quantum Mechanics, by S. Weinberg.
4. Quantum Mechanics (Vols. 1 & 2), by C. Cohen-Tannoudji, B. Diu and F. Laloe.
5. Quantum Mechanics (Vols. 1 & 2), by A. Messiah
6. Quantum Mechanics: Fundamentals, by K. Gottfried and Tung-Mow Yan.
7. Principles of Quantum Mechanics, by P. A. M. Dirac
8. Quantum Mechanics (Non-Relativistic Theory), by L. D. Landau and L. M Lifshitz    

備註 Remarks
     Mastery of physics does not come easily. You must work hard at it, and the work must be done by you, and no one else. 
If you fail to dedicate the serious attention and necessary effort the course needs, you will acquire very little useful skills and knowledge, and this will be reflected in the grade you earn at the end of the course.




